It's believed the victim was killed in a mob justice attack after he was caught robbing people in the area. JOHANNESBURG – Police are probing the death of an 18-year-old youth in Khayelitsha. The young man's body was found dumped in Khayelitsha on Wednesday. It's believed the victim was killed in a mob justice attack after he was caught robbing people in the area. The police's Frederick Van Wyk said: “Circumstances surrounding the death of an 18-year-old man whose body was found behind the Khayelitsha Training Centre are under investigation. We have opened a murder case for further investigation.” (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)